# ESP32 Camera Streaming Prototype

## Overview

This project is an end-to-end embedded systems prototype that captures images using an ESP32-S3 camera, uploads them over Wi-Fi to a Python server, and displays the latest image through a browser-based viewer.

The prototype serves as the communication backbone for a larger environmental sensing platform being developed at the UCLA Human-Computer Interaction Lab. Future work will integrate additional environmental sensors and transition from HTTP-based communication to an MQTT/WebSocket architecture for real-time data streaming.

---

## Features

- ESP32-S3 camera integration
- Wi-Fi connectivity
- JPEG image capture
- HTTP image upload
- Python Flask backend
- Browser-based image viewer
- Real-time image updates

---

## System Architecture

```
                Wi-Fi

        +-------------------+
        |   ESP32-S3 Camera |
        +-------------------+
                  |
          HTTP POST (JPEG)
                  |
                  ▼
        +-------------------+
        | Flask Server      |
        | (Python)          |
        +-------------------+
                  |
          Stores latest.jpg
                  |
                  ▼
        +-------------------+
        | Browser Viewer    |
        +-------------------+
```

